webpackJsonp([0xd0bfadb65a5e],{1283:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Justin Ball",author:"Justin Ball"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/jbasdf/projects/justinball/src/posts/2008-03-30-lifetime-marriage/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>In church today an older lady stood up and said she was grateful for her marriage of 60 years. I was impressed. I think that the divorce today tends to discourage people from believing that they can spend a lifetime with another person. It seems rare to find a couple that has been together for 60 years not just because of divorce but also because of health. Whenever I see a couple that is celebrating half a century together that accomplishment feels far more significant than all the awards, the academic degrees, or political achievements one can accumulate.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"Lifetime Marriage",date:"March 30, 2008",imageUrl:null,image:null}}},pathContext:{path:"/lifetime-marriage"}}}});
